Polish Stocks: Bogdanka, Cersanit, E-Star, Tauron Shares Move

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-03-22T10:04:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/polish-stocks-bogdanka-cersanit-e-star-tauron-shares-move.html
Poland ’s WIG20 Index fell for the
first time in four days, losing 10.53, or 0.4 percent, to
2,782.04 at 10:31 a.m. in Warsaw.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Cersanit SA (CST)   dropped for a second day, sliding 0.4
zloty, or 3.3 percent, to 11.91 zloty. Poland’s biggest ceramic
tile producer said its net income was 103.2 million zloty ($36
million) in 2010, below the 123.2 million-zloty mean estimate of
five analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.  E-Star Alternative Energy Service Plc (EST PW) gained 1.2
zloty, or 0.8 percent, to 144.3 zloty as shares of the Hungarian
alternative energy company that renovates and operates heating
systems started trading on the Warsaw Stock Exchange.  Lubelski Wegiel Bogdanka SA (LWB)   fell 0.9 percent to
126.7 zloty as Deutsche Bank AG downgraded Poland’s only
publicly traded coal producer to “hold.”  Tauron Polska Energia SA (TPE)   sank 0.24 zloty, or 3.8
percent, to 6.15 zloty, heading for the lowest close in a month.
The Polish government is selling up to 209 million shares, or
11.9 percent, in its second-largest utility, according to terms
of the offer obtained by Bloomberg News late yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
